ck the four triples are solutions**:\n   - `(2, 2, 2)`:\n     - `2·2 - 2 = 2`, `2·2 - 2 = 2`, `2·2 - 2 = 2`. All powers of 2 (`2^1`).\n   - `(2, 2, 3)`:\n     - `2·2 - 3 = 1 = 2^0`,\n     - `2·3 - 2 = 4 = 2²`,\n     - `3·2 - 2 = 4 = 2²`.\n   - `(2, 6, 11)`:\n     - `2·6 - 11 = 1 = 2⁰`,\n     - `6·11 - 2 = 64 = 2⁶`,\n     - `11·2 - 6 = 16 = 2⁴`.\n   - `(3, 5, 7)`:\n     - `3·5 - 7 = 8 = 2³`,\n     - `5·7 - 3 = 32 = 2⁵`,\n     - `7·3 - 5 = 16 = 2⁴`.\n\n2. **No other triples satisfy the condition**:\n   - This is the difficult part. We need to:\n     - For each possible value of `a`, `b`, `c` with `a ≤ b ≤ c`, check whether the three expressions are powers of 2. \n     - Since powers of 2 grow quickly, we can try `a` from 1 to 10 and see that no other triples satisfy all three.\n   - Here’s a sketch:\n     - For `a = 1`, try `b = 1`, then `c ≥ 1`. But `ab - c = 1 - c = 2^d ≥ 0` implies `c ≤ 1`, so `c = 1`. But `ab - c = 0`, which is not a power of 2 (`d` natural). Hence no solution.\n     - For `a = 1`, `b = 2`, `c ≥ 2`:\n       - `ab - c = 2 - c = 2^d ≥ 0` ⇒ `c ≤ 2`, so `c = 2`:\n         - `ab - c = 0`, invalid. No solution. \n     - For `a = 1`, other `b` similarly give `ab - c = b - c ≤ 0`, but `b - c = 2^d ≥ 1` is impossible. Hence no solution for `a = 1`.\n     - For `a = 2`, `b = 2` (`a ≤ b`):\n       - `ab - c = 4 - c = 2^d ≥ 0` ⇒ `c ≤ 4`. Possible `c = 2, 3, 4`.\n         - `c = 2`: Already in the list.\n         - `c = 3`: Checked earlier, works.\n         - `c = 4`: Check other conditions:\n           - `bc - a = 8 - 2 = 6`, not a power of 2.\n         So only `c = 2, 3` work.\n     - For `a = 2`, `b = 3` (`a ≤ b`):\n       - `ab - c = 6 - c = 2^d ≥ 0` ⇒ `c ≤ 6`. Also `b ≤ c` ⇒ `c ≥ 3`.\n         - `c = 3`: `ab - c = 3 = 2^?`, no.\n         - `c = 4`: `ab - c = 2`, and `bc - a = 12 - 2 = 10`, not a power of 2.\n         - `c = 5`: `ab - c = 1`, `bc - a = 15 - 2 = 13`, no.\n         - `c = 6`: `ab - c = 0`, no.\n       No solutions.\n     - For `a = 2`, `b = 4`:\n       - `ab - c = 8 - c ≥ 0`, `c ≤ 8`. Also `c ≥ 4`.\n         - `c = 4`: `ab - c = 4`, `bc - a = 16 - 2 = 14`, no.\n         - `c = 5`: `ab - c = 3`, no.\n         - Similarly, no solutions.\n     - For `a = 2`, `b = 5`:\n       - `ab - c = 10 - c ≥ 0`, `c ≤ 10`, `c ≥ 5`.\n         - Trying `c = 5`: `10 - 5 = 5`, no.\n         - No solutions.\n     - For `a = 2`, `b = 6` (`a ≤ b`):\n       - `ab - c = 12 - c ≥ 0`, `c ≤ 12`. Also `c ≥ 6`.\n         - `c = 6`: `ab - c = 6`, no.\n         - `c = 7`: `ab - c = 5`, no.\n         - `c = 8`: `ab - c = 4`, `bc - a = 48 - 2 = 46`, no.\n         - `c = 9`: `ab - c = 3`, no.\n         - `c = 10`: `ab - c = 2`, `bc - a = 60 - 2 = 58`, no.\n         - `c = 11`: `ab - c = 1`, and `bc - a = 66 - 2 = 64`, `ca - b = 22 - 6 = 16`, which is in the list.\n         - `c = 12`: `ab - c = 0`, no.\n       So `(2, 6, 11)` is the only new solution here.\n     - For `a = 3`, `b = 3`:\n       - `ab - c = 9 - c ≥ 0`, `c ≤ 9`, `c ≥ 3`.\n         - `c = 3`: `ab - c = 6`, no.\n         - `c = 4`: `ab - c = 5`, no.\n         - No solutions.\n     - For `a = 3`, `b = 4`:\n       - `ab - c = 12 - c ≥ 0`, `c ≤ 12`, `c ≥ 4`.\n         - `c = 4`: `ab - c = 8`, `bc - a = 16 - 3 = 13`, no.\n         -",
      "\n  have h_main : {(a, b, c) | (a : ℤ) (b : ℤ) (c : ℤ) (h₀ : 0 < a ∧ 0 < b ∧ 0 < c) (h₁ : a ≤ b ∧ b ≤ c) (h₂ : ∃ d : ℕ, a * b - c = 2 ^ d) (h₃ : ∃ d : ℕ, b * c - a = 2 ^ d) (h₄ : ∃ d : ℕ, c * a - b = 2 ^ d)} = {(2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 3), (2, 6, 11), (3, 5, 7)} := by\n    classical\n    ext ⟨a, b, c⟩\n    simp only [Set.mem_setOf_eq, Set.mem_insert_iff, Set.mem_singleton_iff]\n    constructor\n    · -- Prove the forward direction: if (a, b, c) satisfies the conditions, then it is one of the four tuples.\n      intro h\n      rcases h with ⟨ha, hb, hc, habc, h₁, h₂, h₃⟩\n      have h₅ : a ≤ b := habc.1\n      have h₆ : b ≤ c := habc.2\n      have h₇ : 0 < a := ha\n      have h₈ : 0 < b := hb\n      have h₉ : 0 < c := hc\n      -- Normalize the variables to natural numbers\n      have h₁₀ : (a : ℕ) ≤ b := by exact_mod_cast h₅\n      have h₁₁ : (b : ℕ) ≤ c := by exact_mod_cast h₆\n      -- Handle the cases where a, b, c are small\n      have h₁₂ : (a : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by\n        by_contra! h₁₃\n        have h₁₄ : (a : ℕ) ≥ 11 := by linarith\n        have h₁₅ : (b : ℕ) ≥ 11 := by\n          by_contra! h₁₆\n          have h₁₇ : (b : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by linarith\n          have h₁₈ : (b : ℕ) ≥ a := by exact_mod_cast (by linarith)\n          have h₁₉ : (a : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by linarith\n          interval_cases a <;> interval_cases b <;> norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try {\n              rcases h₁ with ⟨d, h₁⟩\n              rcases h₂ with ⟨e, h₂⟩\n              rcases h₃ with ⟨f, h₃⟩\n              norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                (try omega) <;>\n                (try {\n                  have h₂₀ : d ≤ 20 := by\n                    by_contra! h₂₁\n                    have h₂₂ : (2 : ℕ) ^ d ≥ 2 ^ 21 := by\n                      apply pow_le_pow_right\n                      · norm_num\n                      · linarith\n                    norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try nlinarith)\n                  have h₂₃ : e ≤ 20 := by\n                    by_contra! h₂₄\n                    have h₂₅ : (2 : ℕ) ^ e ≥ 2 ^ 21 := by\n                      apply pow_le_pow_right\n                      · norm_num\n                      · linarith\n                    norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try nlinarith)\n                  have h₂₆ : f ≤ 20 := by\n                    by_contra! h₂₇\n                    have h₂₈ : (2 : ℕ) ^ f ≥ 2 ^ 21 := by\n                      apply pow_le_pow_right\n                      · norm_num\n                      · linarith\n                    norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try nlinarith)\n                  interval_cases d <;> interval_cases e <;> interval_cases f <;> norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                    (try omega) <;>\n                    (try nlinarith)\n                })\n            })\n          <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try nlinarith)\n        have h₂₀ : (c : ℕ) ≥ 11 := by\n          by_contra! h₂₁\n          have h₂₂ : (c : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by linarith\n          have h₂₃ : (c : ℕ) ≥ b := by exact_mod_cast (by linarith)\n          have h₂₄ : (b : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by linarith\n          interval_cases b <;> interval_cases c <;> norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try {\n              rcases h₁ with ⟨d, h₁⟩\n              rcases h₂ with ⟨e, h₂⟩\n              rcases h₃ with ⟨f, h₃⟩\n              norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                (try omega) <;>\n                (try {\n                  have h₂₅ : d ≤ 20 := by\n                    by_contra! h₂₆\n                    have h₂₇ : (2 : ℕ) ^ d ≥ 2 ^ 21 := by\n                      apply pow_le_pow_right\n                      · norm_num\n                      · linarith\n                    norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try nlinarith)\n                  have h₂₈ : e ≤ 20 := by\n                    by_contra! h₂₉\n                    have h₃₀ : (2 : ℕ) ^ e ≥ 2 ^ 21 := by\n                      apply pow_le_pow_right\n                      · norm_num\n                      · linarith\n                    norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try nlinarith)\n                  have h₃₁ : f ≤ 20 := by\n                    by_contra! h₃₂\n                    have h₃₃ : (2 : ℕ) ^ f ≥ 2 ^ 21 := by\n                      apply pow_le_pow_right\n                      · norm_num\n                      · linarith\n                    norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try nlinarith)\n                  interval_cases d <;> interval_cases e <;> interval_cases f <;> norm_num at h₁ h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;>\n                    (try omega) <;>\n                    (try nlinarith)\n                })\n            })\n          <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try nlinarith)\n        -- Use the fact that a, b, c are large to derive a contradiction\n        have h₂₅ : (a : ℕ) * b ≥ 11 * b := by\n          nlinarith\n        have h₂₆ : (a : ℕ) * b - c ≥ 11 * b - c := by\n          omega\n        have h₂₇ : 11 * b - c > 0 := by\n          have h₂₈ : (b : ℕ) ≥ 11 := by exact_mod_cast h₁₅\n          have h₂₉ : (c : ℕ) ≥ b := by exact_mod_cast (by linarith)\n          have h₃₀ : (c : ℕ) < 11 * b := by\n            nlinarith\n          omega\n        rcases h₁ with ⟨d, h₁⟩\n        have h₃₁ : (a : ℕ) * b - c = 2 ^ d := by\n          norm_cast at h₁ ⊢ <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try nlinarith)\n        have h₃₂ : 2 ^ d ≥ 11 * b - c := by\n          omega\n        have h₃₃ : 2 ^ d < 11 * b := by\n          have h₃₄ : (a : ℕ) * b - c < 11 * b := by\n            have h₃₅ : (a : ℕ) * b - c < 11 * b := by\n              have h₃₆ : (c : ℕ) ≥ b := by exact_mod_cast (by linarith)\n              have h₃₇ : (a : ℕ) * b < 11 * b + c := by\n                nlinarith\n              omega\n            omega\n          omega\n        have h₃₄ : 2 ^ d < 11 * b := by\n          omega\n        have h₃₅ : 2 ^ d ≥ 11 * b - c := by\n          omega\n        have h₃₆ : 11 * b - c ≤ 2 ^ d := by\n          omega\n        have h₃₇ : d ≤ 3 * b := by\n          by_contra! h₃₈\n          have h₃₉ : d ≥ 3 * b + 1 := by omega\n          have h₄₀ : 2 ^ d ≥ 2 ^ (3 * b + 1) := by\n            apply pow_le_pow_right\n            · norm_num\n            · omega\n          have h₄₁ : 2 ^ (3 * b + 1) > 11 * b := by\n            have h₄₂ : b ≥ 11 := by exact_mod_cast h₁₅\n            have h₄₃ : 2 ^ (3 * b + 1) > 11 * b := by\n              have h₄₄ : ∀ k : ℕ, k ≥ 11 → 2 ^ (3 * k + 1) > 11 * k := by\n                intro k hk\n                induction' hk with k hk IH\n                · norm_num\n                · cases k with\n                  | zero => contradiction\n                  | succ k =>\n                    cases k with\n                    | zero => contradiction\n                    | succ k =>\n                      cases k with\n                      | zero => contradiction\n                      | succ k =>\n                        cases k with\n                        | zero => contradiction\n                        | succ k =>\n                          cases k with\n                          | zero => contradiction\n                          | succ k =>\n                            cases k with\n                            | zero => contradiction\n                            | succ k =>\n                              cases k with\n                              | zero => contradiction\n                              | succ k =>\n                                cases k with\n                                | zero => contradiction\n                                | succ k =>\n                                  simp_all [Nat.mul_succ, pow_add, pow_one, pow_mul]\n                                  <;>\n                                  nlinarith [pow_pos (by norm_num : (0 : ℕ) < 2) k]\n              exact h₄₄ b h₄₂\n            exact h₄₃\n          have h₄₅ : 2 ^ d > 11 * b := by\n            linarith\n          omega\n        have h₃₈ : d ≤ 3 * b := by\n          omega\n        -- Use the fact that d is bounded to find a contradiction\n        interval_cases d <;> norm_num at h₃₁ ⊢ <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try {\n            have h₃₉ : (a : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by\n              nlinarith\n            omega\n          }) <;>\n          (try {\n            have h₃₉ : (a : ℕ) ≤ 10 := by\n              nlinarith\n            interval_cases a <;> norm_num at h₃₁ ⊢ <;>\n              (try omega) <;>\n              (try {\n                have h₄₀ : (b : ℕ) ≤ 20 := by\n                  nlinarith\n                interval_cases b <;> norm_num at h₃₁ ⊢ <;>\n                  (try omega) <;>\n                  (try {\n                    have h₄₁ : (c : ℕ) ≤ 40 := by\n                      nlinarith\n                    interval_cases c <;> norm_num at h₃₁ ⊢ <;>\n                      (try omega) <;>\n                      (try {\n                        rcases h₂ with ⟨e, h₂⟩\n                        rcases h₃ with ⟨f, h₃⟩\n                        norm_num at h₂ h₃ ⊢ <;",
      "\n  have h_subset₁ : {(a, b, c) | (a : ℤ) (b : ℤ) (c : ℤ) (h₀ : 0 < a ∧ 0 < b ∧ 0 < c) (h₁ : a ≤ b ∧ b ≤ c) (h₂ : ∃ d : ℕ, a * b - c = 2^d) (h₃ : ∃ d : ℕ, b * c - a = 2^d) (h₄ : ∃ d : ℕ, c * a - b = 2^d)} ⊆ answer({(2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 3), (2, 6, 11), (3, 5, 7)}) := by sorry\n  have h_subset₂ : answer({(2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 3), (2, 6, 11), (3, 5, 7)}) ⊆ {(a, b, c) | (a : ℤ) (b : ℤ) (c : ℤ) (h₀ : 0 < a ∧ 0 < b ∧ 0 < c) (h₁ : a ≤ b ∧ b ≤ c) (h₂ : ∃ d : ℕ, a * b - c = 2^d) (h₃ : ∃ d : ℕ, b * c - a = 2^d) (h₄ : ∃ d : ℕ, c * a - b = 2^d)} := by sorry\n  have h_main : {(a, b, c) | (a : ℤ) (b : ℤ) (c : ℤ) (h₀ : 0 < a ∧ 0 < b ∧ 0 < c) (h₁ : a ≤ b ∧ b ≤ c) (h₂ : ∃ d : ℕ, a * b - c = 2^d) (h₃ : ∃ d : ℕ, b * c - a = 2^d) (h₄ : ∃ d : ℕ, c * a - b = 2^d)} = answer({(2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 3), (2, 6, 11), (3, 5, 7)}) := by\n    apply Set.Subset.antisymm\n    · exact h_subset₁\n    · exact h_subset₂\n  exact h_main",
      "\n  have h_main : {(a, b, c) | (a : ℤ) (b : ℤ) (c : ℤ) (h₀ : 0 < a ∧ 0 < b ∧ 0 < c) (h₁ : a ≤ b ∧ b ≤ c) (h₂ : ∃ d : ℕ, a * b - c = 2^d) (h₃ : ∃ d : ℕ, b * c - a = 2^d) (h₄ : ∃ d : ℕ, c * a - b = 2^d)} = ({(2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 3), (2, 6, 11), (3, 5, 7)} : Set (ℤ × ℤ × ℤ)) := by\n    apply Set.Subset.antisymm\n    · -- Prove the forward inclusion\n      intro ⟨a, b, c⟩ h\n      simp only [Set.mem_setOf_eq, Set.mem_insert_iff, Set.mem_singleton_iff] at h ⊢\n      rcases h with ⟨a, b, c, h₀, h₁, h₂, h₃, h₄, rfl⟩\n      norm_cast at h₀ h₁ h₂ h₃ h₄ ⊢\n      have h₅ : a > 0 := by linarith\n      have h₆ : b > 0 := by linarith\n      have h₇ : c > 0 := by linarith\n      have h₈ : a ≤ b := by linarith\n      have h₉ : b ≤ c := by linarith\n      -- We now consider different cases to find all possible solutions\n      have h₁₀ : (a, b, c) = (2, 2, 2) ∨ (a, b, c) = (2, 2, 3) ∨ (a, b, c) = (2, 6, 11) ∨ (a, b, c) = (3, 5, 7) := by\n        -- We will prove that the only solutions are the ones listed\n        have h₁₁ : ∃ d : ℕ, a * b - c = 2^d := h₂\n        have h₁₂ : ∃ d : ℕ, b * c - a = 2^d := h₃\n        have h₁₃ : ∃ d : ℕ, c * a - b = 2^d := h₄\n        -- We consider the possible values of a, b, c and check each case\n        have h₁₄ : a ≤ 12 := by\n          by_contra! h₁₆\n          -- If a > 12, we derive a contradiction\n          have h₁₇ : a ≥ 13 := by linarith\n          have h₁₈ : b ≥ a := by linarith\n          have h₁₉ : c ≥ b := by linarith\n          have h₂₀ : b ≥ 13 := by linarith\n          have h₂₁ : c ≥ 13 := by linarith\n          -- Using the inequalities, we show that no such a, b, c exist\n          rcases h₁₁ with ⟨d, h₁₁⟩\n          have h₂₂ : a * b - c = 2 ^ d := by exact_mod_cast h₁₁\n          have h₂₃ : 2 ^ d > 0 := by positivity\n          have h₂₄ : (a : ℕ) * b - c = 2 ^ d := by\n            have h₂₅ : (a : ℕ) * b ≥ c := by\n              have h₂₆ : (a : ℕ) * b ≥ 13 * b := by nlinarith\n              have h₂₇ : 13 * b ≥ 13 * a := by nlinarith\n              have h₂₈ : 13 * a ≥ 13 * 13 := by nlinarith\n              nlinarith\n            omega\n          have h₂₅ : (a : ℕ) * b - c = 2 ^ d := by exact_mod_cast h₂₄\n          have h₂₆ : (a : ℕ) * b ≥ 13 * b := by nlinarith\n          have h₂₇ : 13 * b ≥ 13 * a := by nlinarith\n          have h₂₈ : 13 * a ≥ 13 * 13 := by nlinarith\n          have h₂₉ : (a : ℕ) * b ≥ 13 * 13 := by nlinarith\n          have h₃₀ : 2 ^ d ≥ (a : ℕ) * b - c := by\n            omega\n          have h₃₁ : 2 ^ d < (a : ℕ) * b := by\n            have h₃₂ : c ≥ 1 := by linarith\n            have h₃₃ : (a : ℕ) * b - c < (a : ℕ) * b := by\n              omega\n            omega\n          have h₃₂ : 2 ^ d < (a : ℕ) * b := by omega\n          have h₃₃ : 2 ^ d ≥ (a : ℕ) * b - c := by omega\n          have h₃₄ : (a : ℕ) * b - c < (a : ℕ) * b := by\n            omega\n          have h₃₅ : 2 ^ d < (a : ℕ) * b := by omega\n          have h₃₆ : 2 ^ d ≥ (a : ℕ) * b - c := by omega\n          -- Using the inequalities, we show that no such a, b, c exist\n          have h₃₇ : d ≤ 2 * a := by\n            by_contra! h₃₈\n            have h₃₉ : d ≥ 2 * a + 1 := by linarith\n            have h₄₀ : 2 ^ d ≥ 2 ^ (2 * a + 1) := by\n              exact pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num) (by linarith)\n            have h₄₁ : 2 ^ (2 * a + 1) > (a : ℕ) * b := by\n              have h₄₂ : (a : ℕ) ≥ 13 := by exact_mod_cast h₁₇\n              have h₄₃ : 2 ^ (2 * a + 1) > (a : ℕ) * b := by\n                have h₄₄ : 2 ^ (2 * a + 1) = 2 * (2 ^ (2 * a)) := by\n                  ring_nf\n                  <;> simp [pow_add, pow_mul, pow_one]\n                  <;> ring_nf\n                have h₄₅ : (a : ℕ) * b ≤ (a : ℕ) * c := by\n                  nlinarith\n                have h₄₆ : (a : ℕ) * c ≤ (a : ℕ) * c := by nlinarith\n                have h₄₇ : 2 ^ (2 * a) ≥ 2 ^ (2 * 13) := by\n                  apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n                  nlinarith\n                have h₄₈ : 2 ^ (2 * 13)